***********************Linux Installation Guide**************************
Following software and packages need to be installed on Linux-ubuntu
before you run the grass script

1. Grass
2. Python 
  2.1 numpy
  2.2 scipy
  2.3 pylab
  2.4 rpy
  2.5 yaml


RunMe.sh contain executable shell script code which will automatically 
install the given packages and softwares for you.

To run the RunMe.sh file 
  --> select the file -> press enter--> click on Execute
  OR
  --> open the terminal to the directory in which RunMe.sh file is placed
     using cd (change directory) command
     type "sh RunMe.sh" and press enter

*****************After Installation********************
1. Specify the parameters for landscape simulation in parameters.yaml file
   in source code directory.
2. Now to run the simulation code, go to source code directory using cd command in terminal
   and type "python main.py" (without quotes) and press enter. 
